  <!-- Main Content -->
  <section class="bg-[#F5F5F0] pb-16">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 max-w-4xl">

      <div class="bg-navy/5 border-l-4 border-gold rounded-r-lg p-4 mb-6">
        <p class="text-sm text-text-light leading-relaxed italic">The Alfa Laval MAB 104 centrifuge is a manual-clean solid-bowl disc stack centrifuge rated at 10 GPM (7 GPM on diesel). Dolphin Centrifuge supplies the MAB 104 as the DMB-007 complete centrifuge module — a fully integrated system with controls and piping for diesel, biodiesel, and lube oil purification. The stainless steel variant (DMB-007S / WSB 104) is available for corrosive fluid applications. Based in Warren, Michigan, Dolphin Centrifuge has over 40 years of experience in MAB-series centrifuge systems.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Overview -->
      <div id="overview" class="bg-white rounded-xl border border-gray-100 shadow-sm p-6 md:p-8 mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#1B3A5C] mb-4" style="font-family: 'Plus Jakarta Sans', sans-serif;">Overview</h2>
        <p class="text-[#2D2D2D] mb-4">
          The Alfa Laval MAB 104 Centrifuge is a solid-retaining (aka solid bowl; manual-clean), disc-stack centrifuge ideal for the continuous, three-phase separation of fuels, such as <a href="/diesel-centrifuge/" class="text-[#1B3A5C] underline hover:text-[#E8A317]">diesel</a>, <a href="/biodiesel-centrifuge/" class="text-[#1B3A5C] underline hover:text-[#E8A317]">biodiesel</a>, and <a href="/lube-oil-centrifuge/" class="text-[#1B3A5C] underline hover:text-[#E8A317]">turbine lube oil</a>.
        </p>
        <p class="text-[#2D2D2D] mb-4">
          With a 2 HP Motor, the MAB 104 centrifuge has a bowl RPM of 7,500 and can process 6 GPM of Diesel Fuel or 1 GPM of Turbine Lube Oil.
        </p>
        <p class="text-[#2D2D2D] mb-4">
          The MAB 104 is one of the most versatile manual-clean centrifuge models in the Alfa Laval product range. It bridges the gap between the smaller MAB 103 and the larger MAB 204 series, making it suitable for a wide range of industrial and marine applications where moderate throughput capacity is required. Its compact footprint and robust construction make it a popular choice for both onshore installations and offshore platforms.
        </p>
        <p class="text-[#2D2D2D] mb-4">
          As a solid-retaining centrifuge, the MAB 104 does not have an automatic discharge mechanism. Instead, separated solids accumulate in the bowl periphery and must be removed manually during scheduled maintenance stops. This design simplifies the centrifuge construction, reduces maintenance complexity, and makes the MAB 104 particularly well-suited for applications with relatively low solids content where continuous solids discharge is not required.
        </p>
        <div class="flex justify-center mt-4">
          <figure class="text-center">
            <img
              src="/images/alfa-laval-mab-104-centrifuge/Alfa-Laval-MAB104-XP-NOV-e1613927321646.jpg"
              alt="Alfa Laval MAB 104 Explosion Proof Centrifuge for offshore and hazardous locations"
              width="250" height="300"
              loading="lazy"
              class="rounded-lg shadow mx-auto"
            />
            <figcaption class="text-sm text-gray-500 mt-2">Alfa Laval MAB 104 Explosion Proof Centrifuge</figcaption>
          </figure>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Specifications -->
      <div id="specifications" class="bg-white rounded-xl border border-gray-100 shadow-sm p-6 md:p-8 mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#1B3A5C] mb-4" style="font-family: 'Plus Jakarta Sans', sans-serif;">Specifications</h2>

        <p class="text-[#2D2D2D] mb-4">
          The following table provides the complete technical specifications for the Alfa Laval MAB 104 B 24-60 centrifuge, including capacity ratings for various fluid types, physical dimensions, weight, and electrical requirements. The dimensions drawing below shows the footprint of the bare centrifuge unit without ancillary equipment.
        </p>

        <div class="flex justify-center mb-6">
          <figure class="text-center w-full">
            <img
              src="/images/alfa-laval-mab-104-centrifuge/Alfa-Laval-MAB-104-Dimensions-600.jpg"
              alt="Alfa Laval MAB 104 Centrifuge Dimensions drawing — 30 x 38 x 43 inches"
              width="600" height="355"
              loading="lazy"
              class="rounded-lg shadow mx-auto w-full max-w-xl"
            />
            <figcaption class="text-sm text-gray-500 mt-2">Alfa Laval MAB 104 Dimensions</figcaption>
          </figure>
        </div>

        <div class="overflow-x-auto mb-8">
          <table class="w-full text-sm border-collapse">
            <thead>
              <tr class="bg-[#1B3A5C] text-white">
                <th class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2 text-left">Parameter</th>
                <th class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2 text-left">Alfa Laval MAB 104 B 24-60</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr class="bg-gray-50">
                <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-2 font-medium">Centrifuge Model</td>
                <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-2 font-mono">Alfa Laval MAB 104 B 24-60</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-2 font-medium">Capacity — Diesel</td>
                <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-2 font-mono">6 GPM on 13 cSt Diesel Fuel</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="bg-gray-50">
                <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-2 font-medium">Capacity — Turbine Lube Oil</td>
                <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-2 font-mono">5 GPM</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-2 font-medium">Capacity — Hydraulic Oil</td>
                <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-2 font-mono">4 GPM</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="bg-gray-50">
                <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-2 font-medium">Sludge Space</td>
                <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-2 font-mono">0.25 Gallons</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-2 font-medium">Bowl Speed</td>
                <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-2 font-mono">8,100 RPM</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="bg-gray-50">
                <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-2 font-medium">Net Weight</td>
                <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-2 font-mono">400 Lbs.</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-2 font-medium">Dimensions</td>
                <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-2 font-mono">30" x 38" x 43" (Bare Centrifuge)</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="bg-gray-50">
                <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-2 font-medium">Motor Power</td>
                <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-2 font-mono">2 HP</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-2 font-medium">Voltages</td>
                <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-2 font-mono">230 / 460 V or 110 V Single Phase</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <!-- Material of Construction -->
        <div id="material-of-construction">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-[#1B3A5C] mb-3" style="font-family: 'Plus Jakarta Sans', sans-serif;">Material of Construction</h3>
          <p class="text-[#2D2D2D] mb-4">
            The Alfa Laval MAB 104 is designed for mineral oil and fuel separation applications. Therefore, the material used in its construction is well suited for such uses. The following table lists the various components of the centrifuge and the material it is made of.
          </p>
          <div class="overflow-x-auto">
            <table class="w-full text-sm border-collapse">
              <thead>
                <tr class="bg-[#1B3A5C] text-white">
                  <th class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2 text-left">Component</th>
                  <th class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2 text-left">Material</th>
                </tr>
              </thead>
              <tbody>
                <tr class="bg-gray-50">
                  <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-2">Bowl Body &amp; Bowl Hood</td>
                  <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-2 font-mono">316L Duplex Stainless Steel</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-2">Disc Stack</td>
                  <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-2 font-mono">316L Duplex Stainless Steel</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="bg-gray-50">
                  <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-2">Distributor or Disc Carrier</td>
                  <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-2 font-mono">Marine Grade Bronze or 316 Stainless Steel (Special Order)</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-2">Top Disc</td>
                  <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-2 font-mono">Marine Grade Bronze or 316 Stainless Steel (Special Order)</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="bg-gray-50">
                  <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-2">Top Covers (Collecting)</td>
                  <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-2 font-mono">Silium (Aluminum Alloy)</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-2">Frame</td>
                  <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-2 font-mono">Nodular Cast Iron</td>
                </tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- FAQ Callout -->
      <div class="bg-[#1B3A5C] bg-opacity-5 border-l-4 border-[#E8A317] rounded-r-lg p-4 mb-8">
        <p class="text-[#2D2D2D] italic">
          If you have simple, routine questions: We have condensed our 40+ years of disc-stack centrifuge experience into <a href="/disc-stack-centrifuge-faq/" class="text-[#1B3A5C] underline font-semibold hover:text-[#E8A317]">101 Frequently Asked Questions about Disc Stack Centrifuges!</a>
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Applications -->
      <div id="applications" class="bg-white rounded-xl border border-gray-100 shadow-sm p-6 md:p-8 mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#1B3A5C] mb-4" style="font-family: 'Plus Jakarta Sans', sans-serif;">Applications</h2>
        <p class="text-[#2D2D2D] mb-4">
          The <strong>Alfa Laval MAB-104</strong> is a purifier type disc-stack centrifuge. It is designed to separate water (moisture) and fine sediment from mineral oil and lubricating oil. It is primarily used for purifying fuels such as <a href="/diesel-fuel-purifier/" class="text-[#1B3A5C] underline hover:text-[#E8A317]">diesel</a>, kerosene, etc. The MAB-104 is also used for separating water and fine sediment from <a href="/lube-oil-centrifuge/" class="text-[#1B3A5C] underline hover:text-[#E8A317]">lubrication oil</a>, <a href="/hydraulic-oil-centrifuge/" class="text-[#1B3A5C] underline hover:text-[#E8A317]">hydraulic oil</a>, and other mineral oil.
        </p>
        <p class="text-[#2D2D2D] mb-4">
          For offshore applications, the centrifuge is configured similar to the OCM-104-Ex configuration with explosion-proof ATEX Zone II.
        </p>
        <p class="text-[#2D2D2D] mb-4">
          The MAB 104 centrifuge is widely used across various industries including marine, power generation, manufacturing, and oil and gas. In marine applications, it serves as a fuel oil purifier for diesel engines and generators aboard vessels. In power generation facilities, it purifies turbine lube oil and diesel fuel to ensure optimal equipment performance and longevity. Manufacturing plants use the MAB 104 for maintaining the quality of hydraulic oils and other process fluids.
        </p>
        <p class="text-[#2D2D2D]">
          The three-phase separation capability of the MAB 104 allows it to simultaneously remove both water contamination and solid particulates from the process fluid in a single pass. This makes it more efficient than filters or coalescers that can only address one type of contamination at a time. The centrifuge can remove particles down to sub-micron levels and water content to below 100 ppm, depending on the application and operating conditions.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Modifications -->
      <div id="modifications" class="bg-white rounded-xl border border-gray-100 shadow-sm p-6 md:p-8 mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#1B3A5C] mb-4" style="font-family: 'Plus Jakarta Sans', sans-serif;">Modifications</h2>
        <p class="text-[#2D2D2D] mb-4">
          The MAB 104 centrifuge needs modifications for specific applications such as hazardous area installation, processing of water-based fluids, oil, or fuel. The following is a list of common modifications by Dolphin Centrifuge based on the specific application.
        </p>
        <div class="overflow-x-auto">
          <table class="w-full text-sm border-collapse">
            <thead>
              <tr class="bg-[#1B3A5C] text-white">
                <th class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2 text-left">Centrifuge Modification</th>
                <th class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2 text-left">Application / Purpose</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr class="bg-gray-50">
                <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-2">Direct Drive (Replace Friction Clutch)</td>
                <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-2">Explosion Proof Configuration</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-2">Non-Sparking Friction Blocks</td>
                <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-2">Explosion Proof Configuration</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="bg-gray-50">
                <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-2">Pump Reconfiguration (Capacity)</td>
                <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-2">Lube Oil to Light Fuel <em>OR</em> Light Fuel to Lube Oil</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-2">Seals Elastomer (Viton / EPDM)</td>
                <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-2">Biodiesel, Hemp Ethanol, Corrosive Chemicals, etc.</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="bg-gray-50">
                <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-2">Gear Pump Replacement</td>
                <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-2">Water Based Fluids (Steel Gear Pump not Suitable)</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-2">Operating Frequency Conversion</td>
                <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-2">Adapt to Operating Voltage Frequency (50 or 60 Hz)</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="bg-gray-50">
                <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-2">Special Motor Adaptation</td>
                <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-2">Single Phase (110 V or 220 V) Voltage Application</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-2">Bowl Parts Material Upgrade</td>
                <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-2">Convert Bowl Parts to Stainless Steel (Aqueous Ammonia)</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="bg-gray-50">
                <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-2">Purifier to Clarifier</td>
                <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-2">Convert from 3-Phase to 2-Phase Mode (Clarifier)</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
        <p class="text-[#2D2D2D] mt-4">
          Each modification is performed by Dolphin Centrifuge technicians with extensive experience in rebuilding and reconfiguring Alfa Laval disc-stack centrifuges. All modifications are tested and verified before the centrifuge is shipped to ensure reliable operation in the intended application. The purifier-to-clarifier conversion, for example, involves replacing the three-phase top disc with a two-phase version, changing the centrifuge from a water-and-solids separator (purifier) to a solids-only separator (clarifier).
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Operation -->
      <div id="operation" class="bg-white rounded-xl border border-gray-100 shadow-sm p-6 md:p-8 mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#1B3A5C] mb-4" style="font-family: 'Plus Jakarta Sans', sans-serif;">Operation</h2>
        <p class="text-[#2D2D2D] mb-4">
          The process oil is fed to the rotating centrifuge bowl from the top (1) and is sped-up in the distributor (2). It then enters the disc stack (3), and it is between the discs that the separation occurs.
        </p>
        <div class="flex justify-center my-4">
          <figure class="text-center">
            <img
              src="/images/alfa-laval-mab-104-centrifuge/Alfa-Laval-WSB-203-Centrifuge-Bowl-251x300-1.jpg"
              alt="Alfa Laval MAB 104 Centrifuge Bowl cross-section diagram showing oil, water, and solids separation"
              width="251" height="300"
              loading="lazy"
              class="rounded-lg shadow mx-auto"
            />
            <figcaption class="text-sm text-gray-500 mt-2">MAB 104 Centrifuge Bowl — Separation Flow Diagram</figcaption>
          </figure>
        </div>
        <p class="text-[#2D2D2D] mb-4">
          The high centrifugal force pushes the water and heavy solids to the bowl wall. The solids accumulate here, and the water travels over the top disc (4) and exits the bowl through the open outlet (5).
        </p>
        <p class="text-[#2D2D2D] mb-4">
          The oil (light phase) is moved towards the bowl center and exits the bowl through the open outlet (6).
        </p>
        <p class="text-[#2D2D2D] mb-4">
          The centrifuge needs to be periodically stopped for manual removal of separated solids.
        </p>
        <p class="text-[#2D2D2D]">
          The rotating bowl assembly is mounted on a vertical 'bowl-spindle' (7). A horizontally mounted motor rotates the spindle via a worm-gear.
        </p>
      </div>

