      <!-- FAQ Section -->
      <div id="faq" class="bg-white rounded-xl border border-gray-100 shadow-sm p-6 md:p-8 mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#1B3A5C] mb-6" style="font-family: 'Plus Jakarta Sans', sans-serif;">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

        <div class="space-y-6">
          <div class="border-b border-gray-100 pb-4">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[#1B3A5C] mb-2">What is the capacity of the Alfa Laval MAB 104 centrifuge?</h3>
            <p class="text-[#2D2D2D]">
              The Alfa Laval MAB 104 centrifuge can process 6 GPM of 13 cSt diesel fuel, 5 GPM of turbine lube oil, or 4 GPM of hydraulic oil. The WSB 104 variant processes 2 GPM of water-based synthetic coolant. Actual capacity depends on fluid viscosity, contamination levels, and desired separation quality.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="border-b border-gray-100 pb-4">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[#1B3A5C] mb-2">What is the difference between the MAB 104 and the WSB 104?</h3>
            <p class="text-[#2D2D2D]">
              The MAB 104 is a purifier designed to separate water and sediment from mineral oils and fuels such as diesel, lube oil, and hydraulic oil. The WSB 104 is a concentrator version designed specifically for water-based industrial fluids like machining coolant and washer fluid. A key construction difference is that the WSB 104 features all-stainless-steel bowl components (distributor and top disc are 316L Duplex Stainless Steel) and cast iron top covers instead of the aluminum alloy (Silium) covers used on the MAB 104.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="border-b border-gray-100 pb-4">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[#1B3A5C] mb-2">Can the MAB 104 be used in explosion-proof environments?</h3>
            <p class="text-[#2D2D2D]">
              Yes. The MAB 104 can be configured for explosion-proof operation with modifications including direct drive (replacing the friction clutch) and non-sparking friction blocks. For offshore applications, it is configured similar to the OCM-104-Ex configuration with explosion-proof ATEX Zone II certification. Dolphin Centrifuge regularly supplies explosion-proof MAB 104 modules for offshore platforms and refineries.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[#1B3A5C] mb-2">What modifications are available for the MAB 104?</h3>
            <p class="text-[#2D2D2D]">
              Common modifications include explosion-proof configuration (direct drive, non-sparking friction blocks), pump reconfiguration for different fluid viscosities, seal elastomer changes (Viton or EPDM) for biodiesel or corrosive chemicals, gear pump replacement for water-based fluids, operating frequency conversion (50 or 60 Hz), single-phase motor adaptation (110 V or 220 V), bowl parts material upgrade to stainless steel for aqueous ammonia applications, and purifier-to-clarifier conversion to change from three-phase to two-phase separation mode.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

